  <h2>What Feeds the Decision</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>What failed and how.</strong> A single component is a different story than a failed field.</li>
    <li><strong>Age and history.</strong> Repeated problems on an older system change the math.</li>
    <li><strong>Site conditions.</strong> What the soil and layout allow shapes the options.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Approaching the Choice</h2>
  <p>
    A good provider explains the trade-offs rather than defaulting to the biggest job. The <a href="/resources/septic-installation-replacement/">installation and replacement hub</a> covers how replacements proceed. To weigh your situation, <a href="/request-service/">request septic service</a>.
  </p>

